1. Install Required Software
Install Node.js
Download from:

Node.js Official Website

After installing, check:

node -v
npm -v
2. Install VS Code

Visual Studio Code

Install extensions:

Thunder Client
MongoDB for VS Code
3. Clone Your GitHub Repository

Open terminal in VS Code:

git clone https://github.com/Dnyaneshsasale/WAD.git

Go inside project folder:

cd WAD
4. Install Node Modules

Very important.

Run:

npm install

This installs all packages from package.json.

If packages missing, install manually:

npm install express mongoose dotenv body-parser
5. Create .env File

Inside project folder create:

.env

Add:

PORT=3000
MONGO_URI=your_mongodb_connection_string

Example:

PORT=3000
MONGO_URI=mongodb://username:password@.....
6. Start Server

Run:

node server.js

You should see:

MongoDB Connected
Server is running on port 3000
7. Test APIs

Using Thunder Client

GET
http://localhost:3000/students
POST
http://localhost:3000/add-student

Body:

{
  "name": "Dnyanesh",
  "marks": 95
}
